Write the PHP program to implement the following session functions.
(i)session_register() (ii) session_unset() (iii) session_destroy()

CODE:
<?php
// Start the session
session_start();

// (i) session_register() --> Deprecated
// Instead, we directly assign values to $_SESSION
$_SESSION["username"] = "JohnDoe";
$_SESSION["email"] = "john@example.com";

echo "<h3>Session Variables Registered</h3>";
print_r($_SESSION);

// (ii) session_unset() --> removes all session variables but keeps session active
session_unset();

echo "<h3>After session_unset()</h3>";
print_r($_SESSION);

// Re-register again for demo
$_SESSION["username"] = "JohnDoe";
$_SESSION["email"] = "john@example.com";

// (iii) session_destroy() --> destroys the whole session
session_destroy();

echo "<h3>After session_destroy()</h3>";
// Session variables wonâ€™t be accessible after destroy
print_r($_SESSION);
?>

OUTPUT:
Session Variables Registered
Array
(
    [username] => JohnDoe
    [email] => john@example.com
)
After session_unset()
Array
(
)
After session_destroy()
Array
(
    [username] => JohnDoe
    [email] => john@example.com
)
